"{\"uid\": \"myjoyonline.com-paris-olympics-70-teams-qualify-for-relay-events\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Audio By Carbonatix  A total of 70 teams have qualified for relay events at the Paris 2024 Olympic Games following two days of thrilling action at the World Athletics Relays Bahamas 24 (4-5 May)  Fourteen teams in each of the five disciplines being contested in Nassau - the women's and men's 4x100m and 4x400m plus the mixed 4x400m - automatically qualified for Paris places.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 376, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 151, \"end\": 166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9716959707764592, \"rank\": 0.029128482647664752, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 262, \"end\": 268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duchy_of_Nassau\", \"score\": 0.9715932899889541, \"rank\": 0.028851898299108496, \"text\": \"Nassau\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duchy_of_Nassau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duchy_of_Nassau\"}, {\"begin\": 363, \"end\": 368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999995469023478, \"rank\": 4.5309793302771594e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first 40 qualified teams were confirmed on Saturday and the final 30 on Sunday, following a second Olympic qualifying round for teams that missed out on day one.\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 542, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Teams that qualified on Saturday also secured their spots for the respective World Relays finals on Sunday, when they raced for prize money and Olympic lane seeding positions.\", \"from\": 544, \"to\": 719, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"USA won four of the five finals in Nassau, the nation's 4x100m women setting a championship record with their 41.85 run and the mixed 4x400m squad achieving the same with their 3:10.73 performance.\", \"from\": 721, \"to\": 918, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 756, \"end\": 762, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duchy_of_Nassau\", \"score\": 0.9715932899889541, \"rank\": 0.028851898299108496, \"text\": \"Nassau\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duchy_of_Nassau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duchy_of_Nassau\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Botswana's 4x400m men ensured the event ended on a high, running a world lead of 2:59.11 to win the last race of the weekend.\", \"from\": 919, \"to\": 1044, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 919, \"end\": 927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9982057187779982, \"rank\": 0.0016233897646644837, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two nations - Great Britain & Northern Ireland and USA - each qualified a full five teams for Paris, while another six - France, Germany, Italy, Jamaica, Nigeria and Poland - qualified four each.\", \"from\": 1046, \"to\": 1241, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1097, \"end\": 1100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.8674168157064707, \"rank\": 0.1191073075205273, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1140, \"end\": 1145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999995469023478, \"rank\": 4.5309793302771594e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"